80s - ‘92 is their duo era, most synthetic production and the most accordion. Charming in its simplicity and distinct equipment-driven tonality
Mid to late 90s is first full band era, more organic and rock-ish and especially has the most horns due to ska being a thing at the time but still fairly diverse arrangements.
00s is their most maximalist and “produced” stuff, more computer-based instrumentation and sampling. Some songs that veer on fully being electronica or instrumentally hip-hop. They still did rock songs but generally added flair to them
2010s and onwards is much more static, they decided to fall back on their backing band and go with a standard rock configuration providing arrangements easily replicable live. Only like one out of 10 tracks have any adventurous quality to their production or performance and rarely do the more typical songs stand out with how sterile their treatment of them is
